                  <handDesc>
                  <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                  <seg type="rubrication">
                  <foreign xml:lang="gez">ኢግዚአብሔር፡</foreign>
                  <foreign xml:lang="gez">ማርያም፡</foreign>
                  </seg>
                  <desc>The word God is rubricated in the first three works; the word Mary is rubricated in the final two works. Occasionally God is rubricated in alternating red and black letters (e.g., <locus target="#43r" facs="044">fol. 43r</locus>)</desc>
                  <desc>Columetric layout of text: <locus target="#98r #98v" facs="099 100">folss. 98r, 98v, </locus> (tenth biblical canticle); <locus target="#112r #112v" facs="113 114">112r, 112v</locus> (Ps. 150)</desc>
                  </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                  <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d1">
                  Decorative designs:
                  <locus target="#7r #18r #24v #37r #59r #89v #105r #113r #124v #127r" facs="008 019 026 038 060 091 106 114 126 128">folss. 7r, 18r, 24v, 37r, 59r, 89v, 105r, 113r, 124v, 127r, </locus> (crude haräg);
                  <locus target="#44v #53r #59r #63r #68v #69r #72r #78r" facs="046 054 060 064 070 073 079">44v, 53r, 59r, 63r, 68v, 69r, 72r, 78r, </locus> (line of alternating red and black dots);
                  <locus target="#70v" facs="072">70v</locus> (line of red dots)
                  </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                  <list>
                    <item xml:id="e1">
                    <desc>
                    Very poorly copied
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a1">
                    <locus target="#ir(ecto)" facs="001">Fol. ir(ecto)</locus>
                    <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                    Note of secondary ownership, church of Saint George, written upside down in blue ink
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e2">
                    <locus target="#iv(erso)" facs="002">Fol. iv(erso)</locus>
                    <desc>
                    Formula for the beginning of an Amharic letter, Trinitarian formula, written upside down in red and purple ink. Probably pen trials
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e3">
                    <locus target="#128" facs="129">Fol. 128</locus>
                    <desc>
                    pen trials
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e4">
                    <locus target="#117r #117v" facs="118 119">Fols. 117r, 117v</locus>
                    <desc>
                    is secondary and has been added later. r and v and 128v: pen trials
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a2">
                    <locus target="#127v #128r" facs="129">Fols. 127v, 128r</locus>
                    <desc type="Asmat">
                    erased text, written in another hand. Perhaps an asmat prayer against stomach pain
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e5">
                    <locus target="#128v" facs="130">Fol. 128v</locus>
                    <desc>
                    scrawls
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e6">
                    <locus target="#68v #69r" facs="070 070">Fols. 68v, 69r</locus>
                    <desc>
                    Material has been rebound and is out of order. There is a missing quire between 68v (Psalm 111) and 69r (Psalm 120)
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e7">
                    <locus target="#24 #68 #72 #78" facs="025 069 073 079">Fols. 24, 68, 72, 78</locus>
                    <desc>
                    red linen is sewn into the fore edge to mark content as navigaton system;
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e8">
                    <locus target="#59 #63 #101 #113" facs="006 007 011 012">Fols. 59, 63, 101, 113</locus>
                    <desc>
                    white yarn is sewn into the fore edge to mark content as navigation system;
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e9">
                    <locus target="#105" facs="106">Fol. 105</locus>
                    <desc>
                    yellow yarn is sewn into the fore edge to mark content as navigation system
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e10">
                    <locus target="#1v #4r #4v #5r #7v" facs="003 005 006 009">Fols. 1v, 4r, 4v, 5r, 7v</locus>
                    <desc>
                    (etc.) words of text are written interlinearly;
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e11">
                    <locus target="#3v #5v #6r #6v #9v" facs="005 007 007 008 011">Fols. 3v, 5v, 6r, 6v, 9v</locus>
                    <desc>
                    (etc.) lines of text are written interlinearly;
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e12">
                    <locus target="#31r #62r #65r #70r" facs="032 063 066 071">Fols. 31r, 62r, 65r, 70r</locus>
                    <desc>
                    (etc.) erasure markings are visible;
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e13">
                    <locus target="#3v #4r #8r #10v #13v" facs="005 009 012 015">Fols. 3v, 4r, 8r, 10v, 13v</locus>
                    <desc>
                    (etc.) text has been removed
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                  </list>
                </additions>
